{"id": "EUVD-2021-0642", "enisaUuid": "09c39ad4-4561-3b13-9804-ec3aba928947", "description": "fastify-http-proxy is an npm package which is a fastify plugin for proxying your http requests to another server, with hooks. By crafting a specific URL, it is possible to escape the prefix of the proxied backend service. If the base url of the proxied server is `/pub/`, a user expect that accessing `/priv` on the target service would not be possible. In affected versions, it is possible. This is fixed in version 4.3.1.", "datePublished": "2021-03-02T03:35:17", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-03T18:09:15", "baseScore": 10.0, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:H/A:N", "references": ["https://github.com/fastify/fastify-http-proxy/security/advisories/GHSA-c4qr-gmr9-v23w", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2021-21322", "https://github.com/fastify/fastify-http-proxy/commit/02d9b43c770aa16bc44470edecfaeb7c17985016", "https://www.npmjs.com/package/fastify-http-proxy", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2021:3016", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2021:1168"], "aliases": ["CVE-2021-21322", "GHSA-c4qr-gmr9-v23w"], "assigner": "GitHub_M", "epss": 0.45, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "f3049244-1f0c-3257-9609-9c6415f2c65a", "product": {"name": "fastify-http-proxy"}, "product_version": "< 4.3.1"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "c2d07d3e-ada5-3fbc-a9d8-7d45861a7c7f", "vendor": {"name": "fastify"}}], "isExploited": false}